FuncDef: The display bgp vpnv6 routing-table different-origin-as command is used to display the VPNv6 routes with the same destination address but different source AS numbers.
CLIs: display bgp vpnv6 { all | vpn-instance <vpn-instance-name> } routing-table different-origin-as

ParaDef.Info:
Displays all the BGP routes in the specified address family.
-

Specify a VPN-Instance (VRF) name.
The value is a string of 1 to 31 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported. In addition, the VPN instance name must not be _public_. When double quotation marks are used around the string, spaces are allowed in the string.

Examples: <HUAWEI> display bgp vpnv6 all routing-table different-origin-as
Total number of routes from all PE: 0
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The display bgp vpnv6 routing-table different-origin-as command is used to display the VPNv6 routes with the same destination address but different source AS numbers.
